Pour @water{300%ml}(cold, salted) into a #medium pot{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Cook for ~{10%minutes} then remove from the heat and leave aside for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (keep covered so the rice can continue to cook in its own steam).

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Quarter the @mushrooms{125%g}. Chop any larger pieces so all are evenly sized.

Trim the @aubergine{1}(trimmed and chopped into roughly 1cm pieces).

Thinly slice the @chilli{1}(thinly sliced at an angle widthways).

Chop the @lime{1}(chopped into 4 wedges).

Place a #large pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the onion, mushroom and aubergine to the pan and fry until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Season well with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Lower the heat to medium-high then add the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{2%sachets} and fry for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, blend the @baby spinach{120%g} and @coconut milk{1%pack} to make a puree with a #blender{}.

Add the spinach puree to the pan and mix well to coat the veg.

Cover and simmer for ~{8-10%minutes}. Loosen with a splash of @water{to taste} if necessary.

Season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and lime juice—all to taste!

> TIP: If you don't have a blender, finely chop the spinach instead.

Roughly chop the @coriander{10%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Stir the coriander through the cooked rice.

Divide the curry and coriander rice between #plates{} or #bowls{}.

Top with the sliced chilli (use less if you don't like spice).

Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside.